616*{'text': 'Eadbald succeeds Ethelbert as king of Kent.'
616*{'text': 'Edwin becomes king of Northumbria.'
616*{'text': 'Oswald of Northumbria flees to Iona.'
616*{'text': 'Adaloald succeeds his father Agilulf as king of the Lombards (approximate date).'
616*{'text': 'Alexandria is captured by Khosrau II of Persia.'
616*{'text': 'The Banu Hashim clan begins to boycott Muhammad.'
616*{'text': 'A shrine on the site of the future Westminster Abbey is founded.'
617*{'text': 'Sigehbert I becomes king of Essex.'
617*{'text': 'Sui Gong Di succeeds Sui Yang Di as emperor of China.'
617*{'text': 'The Persian Army
column2: under the command of General Spahbodh Shaahin
column3: conquers Chalcedon after a long siege.'

column1: 614*{'text': 'The Palace of Diocletian is damaged by the Avars
614*{'text': 'The Persian Empire under general Shahrbaraz captures and sacks Jerusalem; the Church of the Holy Sepulchre is damaged by fire and the True Cross is captured.'
614*{'text': 'The Persians destroy the Ghassanid kingdom.'
614*{'text': 'The Sudarium of Oviedo is taken from Jerusalem.'
615*{'text': 'The Edict of Paris grants extensive rights to the Frankish nobility.'
615*{'text': 'Pippin of Landen becomes Mayor of the Austrasian Palace.'
615*{'text': 'Edwin of Northumbria takes refuge in East Anglia; he marries Cwenburga
615*{'text': 'The Turks invade China.'
615*{'text': "Sak K'uk' is succeeded by Pacal the Great as ruler of Palenque."
615*{'date': 'October 19'
column2: 'text': 'Pope Adeodatus I (also known as Deusdedit) succeeds Pope Boniface IV as the 68th pope.'

column1: 688*{'text': 'Emperor Justinian II of the Byzantine Empire defeats the Bulgarians.'
685*{'text': "Sussex attacks Kent
column2: supporting Eadric's claim to the throne held by Hlothhere."

column1: 685*{'text': 'Surrey takes Wessex as its overlord.'
685*{'text': 'The Umayyad caliph Marwan I (684–685) is succeeded by Abd al-Malik ibn Marwan (685–705).'
685*{'text': 'Wu Zetian gives two giant pandas to Japan.'
685*{'date': 'July 23'
column2: 'text': 'Pope John V succeeds Pope Benedict II as the 82nd pope.'

column1: 685*{'text': 'Cuthbert is consecrated bishop of Lindisfarne.'
685*{'text': 'John Maroun is elected as the first patriarch in the Maronite Church.'
685*{'text': 'The Al-Aqsa Mosque is established by early Islam.'
684*{'text': 'Wu Ze Tian takes power in China.'
684*{'text': 'The Ummayad caliph Muawiya II is succeeded by Marwan I.'
684*{'date': 'September 7'
column2: 'text': "A large comet is observed in Japan (it's Japan's oldest observation record of the Halley's Comet)."

column1: 684*{'date': 'November 13'
column2: 'text': 'Emperor Temmu institutes eight titles of eight classes (Yakusa-no-kabane) in Japan.'

column1: 684*{'date': 'November 26'
684*{'date': 'June 26'
column2: 'text': 'Pope Benedict II succeeds Pope Leo II as the 81st pope.'

column1: 687*{'text': 'Egica succeeds Erwig as king of the Visigoths.'
687*{'text': 'Adamnan visits the Northumbrian court of Ecgfrith to ransom Irish captives.'
687*{'date': 'December 15'
column2: 'text': 'Pope Sergius I succeeds Pope Conon as the 84th pope.'

column1: 686*{'text': 'The Kingdom of Kent is attacked and conquered by West Saxons under Caedwalla.'
686*{'text': 'Caedwalla exterminates the Jutes of the Isle of Wight and kills King Arwald.'
686*{'date': 'October 1'
686*{'text': "Emperor Temmu's son
column3: is falsely accused of treason by Jito and forced to commit suicide along with his wife

column1: 681*{'text': 'The Bulgars under Asparukh win the war with the Byzantine Empire; the latter signs a peace treaty
column2: which is considered by most as the birth-date of Bulgaria.'

column1: 681*{'text': 'Wilfrid of York is expelled from Northumbria by Ecgfrith
681*{'text': 'Kutluk Khan revolts and reestablishes the Turkish khaganate.'
681*{'date': 'September 16'
680*{'text': 'The Bulgars subjugate the country of current-day Bulgaria.'
680*{'text': 'Pippin of Herstal becomes Mayor of the Palace.'
680*{'text': 'Erwig deposes Wamba to become king of the Visigoths.'
680*{'date': 'October 10'
column2: 'text': 'The Battle of Karbala results in the martyrdom of Imam Hussein.'

column1: 680*{'text': 'Umayyad caliph Muawiyah I is succeeded by Yazid I ibn Muawiyah.'
680*{'date': 'November 12'
column2: 'text': 'The Sixth Ecumenical Council opens in Constantinople and ends September 16

column1: 683*{'text': 'The reign of Pacal the Great
column2: ruler of Maya state of Palenque

column1: 683*{'text': 'The Umayyad caliph Yazid I (680–683) is succeeded by Muawiya II ibn Yazid (683–684).'
683*{'text': 'Emperor Temmu of Japan decrees that copper coins must be used instead of silver coins.'
682*{'text': 'Jarrow Priory is established by Benedict Biscop in the Kingdom of Northumbria.'
682*{'text': 'The first entry is made in the Welsh chronicle Brut y Tywysogion.'
682*{'text': 'Emperor Temmu of Japan issues a decree forbidding the Japanese-style cap of ranks and garments
column2: and changing them into Chinese ones.'

column1: 682*{'date': 'January 3'
682*{'date': 'August 17'
column2: 'text': 'Pope Leo II succeeds Pope Agatho as the 80th pope.'

column1: 682*{'text': 'The venerable Bede goes to Jarrow.'
